WEBVTT

00:02.800 --> 00:05.166
This is court-ordered mediation.

00:05.200 --> 00:07.339
It's not opt-out mediation

00:07.370 --> 00:10.203
or I-don't_-feel-|ike-it
mediation.

00:10.240 --> 00:12.333
We know that,
but what can we do?

00:12.380 --> 00:13.631
We can't negotiate with a stone.

00:13.680 --> 00:16.069
Yes, but you can lower your ask.

00:16.110 --> 00:18.078
Given the set of facts
I'm looking at,

00:18.110 --> 00:19.475
well, it's way too high.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.408
And the law is far
from clear as to...

00:21.450 --> 00:23.315
Then let's go to court.

00:23.350 --> 00:27.286
Look, the judge doesn't want
to clutter up his docket.

00:27.320 --> 00:28.082
That's why he
empowered me

00:28.120 --> 00:30.350
to keep you here
as long as I want

00:30.390 --> 00:31.425
to reach a compromise.

00:31.460 --> 00:32.620
And I will.

00:32.660 --> 00:34.196
So show me
some movement.

00:34.230 --> 00:37.165
Our client wanted to sue
for $38 million in punitive.

00:37.200 --> 00:38.599
We got her down to 14.

00:38.630 --> 00:40.166
That is movement.

00:40.200 --> 00:42.168
But where is theirs?

00:45.440 --> 00:47.704
Think about a new ask.

00:58.890 --> 01:00.187
I need you to raise your offer.

01:00.220 --> 01:01.551
Oh, come on.

01:01.590 --> 01:03.251
Given the set of facts
I'm looking at,

01:03.290 --> 01:04.848
well, it's way too low.

01:04.890 --> 01:06.596
And the legal issues...

01:06.630 --> 01:07.551
What about their ask?

01:07.600 --> 01:09.568
$12 million for what
was clearly an accident?

01:09.600 --> 01:11.090
$14 million.

01:11.130 --> 01:13.098
Oh, my God.
It keeps going up.

01:13.140 --> 01:14.437
No, it was always
$14 million.

01:14.470 --> 01:17.166
Exactly, because they
won't move.

01:17.210 --> 01:18.632
That's Will Gardner's M.O.

01:18.670 --> 01:21.377
He gets his opposition
negotiating with themselves

01:21.410 --> 01:23.571
so he can just
sit back and...

01:26.220 --> 01:28.245
Okay, the
good news is,

01:28.280 --> 01:30.282
they've agreed to an
increase in their offer.

01:30.320 --> 01:31.639
Really?

01:31.690 --> 01:33.180
Yes--
$100,000.

01:33.220 --> 01:34.414
As a goodwill gesture.

01:34.460 --> 01:35.654
But it's linked
to an equwalent

01:35.690 --> 01:37.226
_ reduction
in your ask.

01:37.260 --> 01:38.579
We're not meeting in the middle.

01:38.630 --> 01:40.257
You are meeting
in the middle.

01:40.300 --> 01:43.121
Everyone's meeting in the
middle, or I keep you here.

01:43.170 --> 01:45.422
This was an unfortunate
aCCIdent...

01:45.470 --> 01:46.539
Wait a minute.

01:46.570 --> 01:48.629
I know Celeste works
under the mistaken impression

01:48.670 --> 01:50.331
that if she says something
enough times,

01:50.370 --> 01:51.302
it'll make it true,

01:51.340 --> 01:54.503
but this wasn't an accident;
this was fraud.

01:54.540 --> 01:57.373
Deposition 101, page 58.

01:57.410 --> 02:00.140
_ "But wasn't this
an aCCIdent, ma'am?" Answer...

02:00.180 --> 02:02.444
No, an accident
is unintentional.

02:02.490 --> 02:05.288
What your client did to me
was intentional.

02:05.320 --> 02:06.753
You sound angry, ma'am.

02:06.790 --> 02:08.849
Do I?

02:10.460 --> 02:13.349
Iguess I am. I...

02:14.500 --> 02:16.365
WILL:
Would you like
to take a break, Maggie?

02:16.400 --> 02:18.322
Can we get you anything
for your pain?

02:18.370 --> 02:19.598
CELESTE:
Thank you, Mr. Gardner.

02:19.640 --> 02:21.289
Why don't we let Maggie
raise her hand

02:21.340 --> 02:23.365
when_she wants to take a break
instead of continually

02:23.410 --> 02:24.604
