into the record?

02:24.640 --> 02:26.608
Wow, Celeste. Cynical much?

02:26.640 --> 02:28.608
Only since your fifth
interruption.
Thank you,

02:28.640 --> 02:29.675
but I don't
need a break.

02:29.710 --> 02:30.699
She doesn't need
a break, Will.

02:30.750 --> 02:32.479
Can I continue now?

02:32.520 --> 02:33.475
WILL:
It's up to you.

02:33.520 --> 02:36.216
CELESTE:
This was all caused
by an accident

02:36.250 --> 02:37.478
four years ago,
wasn't it?

02:37.520 --> 02:38.942
I was in a car accident.

02:38.990 --> 02:41.709
It caused DDD--
degenerative disc disorder.

02:41.760 --> 02:43.387
It's misaligned vertebrae discs.

02:43.430 --> 02:47.719
And Dr. Farland, the man
you are suing, my client,

02:47.760 --> 02:49.421
suggested an
operation.

02:49.470 --> 02:50.562
He did.

02:50.600 --> 02:53.728
He said I needed an SCS--
a spinal cord stimulator.

02:53.770 --> 02:57.228
A device like this?

02:57.270 --> 02:58.760
Our client was given
a chance to choose

02:58.810 --> 03:00.437
which model
to have surgically implanted

03:00.480 --> 03:03.347
from a catalogue
of 12 FDA-approved models.

03:03.380 --> 03:06.770
But she didn't choose any--
that's the defense's point.

03:06.820 --> 03:10.210
Yes, but I expected him to pick
one of the FDA-approved devices.

03:10.250 --> 03:12.411
I was never told _
there was another option.

03:12.460 --> 03:15.315
And what happened after
the operation, Maggie?

03:15.360 --> 03:17.328
The pain was gone.

03:17.360 --> 03:18.827
I was ready
to worship

03:18.860 --> 03:20.555
Dr. Farland.
ALICIA:
But then the pain
came back?

03:20.600 --> 03:22.363
Yes, it was like a
deal with the Devil.

03:22.400 --> 03:23.799
It came back
three times worse.

03:23.830 --> 03:25.866
But that's not why
you brought suit.

03:25.900 --> 03:27.128
No. About a month

03:27.170 --> 03:32.699
after my operation, I received
an itemized bill for the SCS.

03:32.740 --> 03:35.732
On it was listed the
manufacturer and the inventor.

03:35.780 --> 03:37.509
And who was the inventor?

03:37.550 --> 03:39.313
My doctor, Dr. Farland.

03:39.350 --> 03:40.817
And this device
he invented--

03:40.850 --> 03:42.545
it was not FDA-approved?

03:42.590 --> 03:44.444
That's right.

03:44.490 --> 03:47.015
He just implanted it
in me like I was a guinea pig.

03:47.060 --> 03:48.914
MEDIATOR:
I want to sympathize--

03:48.960 --> 03:53.294
I do-- but you can't keep
asking for $14 million.

03:53.330 --> 03:54.592
ALICIA:
Maggie has three children.

03:54.630 --> 03:56.518
She is in _
constant pain.

03:56.570 --> 03:59.289
Her life has been shortened
by a decade.

03:59.340 --> 04:00.489
Her husband left her,

04:00.540 --> 04:01.791
and she's being kicked
out of her house,

04:01.840 --> 04:03.705
all because she cannot
hold down a job

04:03.740 --> 04:05.765
or offer spousal
companionship.

04:05.810 --> 04:07.004
Now, if that happened to me

04:07.040 --> 04:10.999
from a doctor who experimented
on me without my knowledge,

04:11.050 --> 04:14.440
I'm sorry, but I would be asking
for twice as much.

04:20.360 --> 04:22.487
Good job. Keep on him.

04:22.530 --> 04:24.680
And, everyone,
the mediator's threatening

04:24.730 --> 04:26.527
to keep us here
through the weekend,

04:26.560 --> 04:28.755
and I think he means it,
so make arrangements.

04:28.800 --> 04:30.961
(cell phone beeping)

04:31.000 --> 04:32.968
We might have a slight edge
in mediation.

04:33.000 --> 04:34.991
The mediator seems sympathetic.

04:35.040 --> 04:36.803
Really? Will that matter?

04:36.840 --> 04:38.068
Not really.

04:38.110 --> 04:39.805
We're heading to trial
either way,

04:39.840 --> 04:41.307
but it shows _
our argument's working.

04:41.340 --> 04:42.568
What's up there?

04:42.610 --> 04:43.907
