think it's funny.

11:49.170 --> 11:51.161
I thought we were
making progress.

11:51.210 --> 11:53.269
Oh, we are making progress.

11:53.310 --> 11:55.107
Mr. Gardner has a tell.

11:55.140 --> 11:56.869
When he's in trouble,
he doubles down.

11:56.910 --> 12:00.016
So we're lowering
our offer.

12:00.050 --> 12:02.075
You don't you think
the issues here

12:02.120 --> 12:04.111
are too serious
to treat like gambling?

12:04.150 --> 12:07.415
No, gambling is too serious
to treat like these issues.

12:07.460 --> 12:09.212
We're lowering our offer.

12:09.260 --> 12:10.887
(elevator bell dings)

12:12.900 --> 12:14.094
You all right?

12:14.130 --> 12:15.256
No.

12:15.300 --> 12:16.255
Okay.

12:16.300 --> 12:18.928
(cell phone ringing)

12:18.970 --> 12:20.062
Yeah.

12:20.100 --> 12:21.829
What are you doing?

12:21.870 --> 12:23.098
Will wants me to get
some inkling

12:23.140 --> 12:24.368
of their bottom line
in mediation.

12:24.410 --> 12:25.365
Why?

12:25.410 --> 12:26.502
Eli needs your help.

12:26.540 --> 12:29.008
Heather Farms
outside Bloomington.

12:29.040 --> 12:32.100
The USDA is investigating
this listeria outbreak,

12:32.150 --> 12:34.243
and they tend to be slow.

12:34.280 --> 12:36.419
Well, which takes priority,
cheese or mediation?

12:36.450 --> 12:38.315
Both.

12:38.350 --> 12:40.352
All right, got it.

12:40.390 --> 12:42.187
ALICIA: I expect mediation
to extend through the weekend,

12:42.220 --> 12:46.953
at least,
so, um, I will be...

12:47.000 --> 12:48.194
There is no Heather Farms.

12:48.230 --> 12:49.925
It's just one division
of Karpwell Foods.

12:49.970 --> 12:51.164
ELI:
And I don't care.

12:51.200 --> 12:52.565
I'm not your rabbi, sir.

12:52.600 --> 12:54.488
I'm merely trying
to keep your cheese

12:54.540 --> 12:56.804
from damaging the image
of all cheeses.

12:56.840 --> 12:59.434
Well, I'm sorry you feel
that way, but I do care.

12:59.470 --> 13:02.177
It's not even clear
that we're responSIble.

13:02.210 --> 13:04.007
I mean, what else
did these kids eat?

13:04.050 --> 13:05.176
That's what I
want to know.

13:05.210 --> 13:06.507
Oh, yes, that's a great
line of defense.

13:06.550 --> 13:08.518
With images like these,
people love to hear

13:08.550 --> 13:10.586
that the kids
are really the problem.

13:10.620 --> 13:12.144
Do you know
who Tony Hayward is?

13:12.190 --> 13:13.509
Do I...

13:13.560 --> 13:15.915
Yes, he's the CEO
of British Petroleum.

13:15.960 --> 13:17.154
No, ex-CEO of BP.

13:17.190 --> 13:20.250
The man who many think oversaw
the destruction of a brand.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.450
So first thing's first,
we work on your attitude.

13:22.500 --> 13:24.365
Excuse me?
I think we need to work on...

13:24.400 --> 13:26.220
Look, I don't have time
to argue with you.

13:26.270 --> 13:28.261
The first rule_ _
of managing a cri5is:

13:28.300 --> 13:30.006
the top man
answers the questions.

13:30.040 --> 13:32.133
That is the only
reason you're here,

13:32.170 --> 13:34.001
that is the only reason
I am talking to you.

13:34.040 --> 13:35.837
So, in ten minutes time,
you're giving a press conference

13:35.880 --> 13:38.269
where you'll order all your
cheese products off the shelves.

13:38.310 --> 13:39.208
We need a split screen

13:39.250 --> 13:42.413
of that image
with you looking strong--

13:42.450 --> 13:44.247
wrong tie, get him a red tie--

13:44.290 --> 13:45.587
then you'll apologize

13:45.620 --> 13:48.919
for any missteps
and say the buck stops here.

13:48.960 --> 13:50.154
Actually, he can't do that.

13:50.190 --> 13:52.329
Actually, he can and he will.

13:52.360 --> 13:54.555
No, legally,
he's in a very vulnerable spot.

13:54.600 --> 13:56.591
He can't be out there
apologizing and taking blame.

13:56.630 --> 13:58.564
He's gonna get sued
no matter what.

13:58.600 --> 14:00.238
Yes, but the size of the
suit is still in question.

14:00.270 --> 14:01.294
I don't care about
the size of the suit, Diane.

14:01.340 --> 14:02.329
Yes, Eli, but I do.

14:02.370 --> 14:04.338
I'll just sit here then.

14:04.370 --> 14:05.906
Diane, you're only here
as window dressing.

14:05.940 --> 14:07.908
You're only here to keep us
from getting subpoenaed.

14:07.940 --> 14:09.874
No, I'm here as their lawyer.
You're working the images...

14:09.910 --> 14:11.548
And the images
take precedent right now.

14:11.580 --> 14:14.071
Eli, listen to me...
He won't have
a busmess unless he...

14:14.120 --> 14:16.987
Nice to meet you,
Mr. Protopapas.

14:17.020 --> 14:19.079
Dr. Farland was
stopping by for lunch.

14:19.120 --> 14:20.417
But if you have
any questions...

14:22.460 --> 14:25.349
Ms. Serrano,
could I speak with you?

14:25.390 --> 14:26.618
This is
really inappropriate.
We were having lunch.

14:26.660 --> 14:27.797
It's been on the
books for weeks.

14:27.830 --> 14:30.924
I am not listening to any
evidence off the record, ma'am.

14:30.970 --> 14:32.961
And I am not
offering any.

14:33.000 --> 14:34.297
I'm standing
on the record.

14:34.340 --> 14:35.261
So is the plaintiff.

14:35.300 --> 14:36.665
And they offer
a convincing case.

14:36.700 --> 14:39.339
An easily-refuted case.

14:39.370 --> 14:41.406
Mrs. Reeves is responsible
for her own condition.

14:43.250 --> 14:44.308
How do you figure?

14:44.350 --> 14:45.601
Deposition 200,
page 14.

14:45.650 --> 14:48.073
It's so key, I know
it from memory.

14:48.120 --> 14:51.248
"Question: If there's nothing
wrong with your device, Doctor,

14:51.290 --> 14:52.541
how did it malfunction?"

14:52.590 --> 14:53.955
It didn't
malfunction.

14:53.990 --> 14:55.287
Even the best SCSs

14:55.320 --> 14:56.582
are prone to lead migration.

14:56.620 --> 14:58.087
CELESTE:
And a lead is...?

14:58.130 --> 15:00.189
Oh, sorry.

15:00.230 --> 15:02.653
When the electrical leads
don't stay where intended.

15:02.700 --> 15:05.225
It's usually not serious,
but in the case of Maggie,

15:05.270 --> 15:07.238
it became quite serious
because the problem

15:07.270 --> 15:08.965
went undetected
for so long.

15:09.000 --> 15:11.366
That's what caused
the infection,

15:11.410 --> 15:13.275
which caused the permanent
damage to her spine.

15:13.310 --> 15:15.232
And why did it go undetected?

15:15.280 --> 15:17.248
Well, I prescribed
hydromorphone

15:17.280 --> 15:19.305
for any topical pain
from the surgery,

15:19.350 --> 15:22.319
but Mrs. Reeves-_- I'm
sorry to say this--

15:22.350 --> 15:25.148
but she_ continued to use the
painkiller long afterward.

15:25.190 --> 15:28.614
CELESTE:
So, if Mrs. Reeves hadn't
overmedicated herself,

15:28.660 --> 15:30.252
she would have
noticed the infection

15:30.290 --> 15:32.258
and come to you for
her SCS adjustment?

15:32.290 --> 15:33.427
Yes.

15:33.460 --> 15:35.325
I'm sorry, Mrs. Reeves,

15:35.360 --> 15:37.260
but it's true.

15:37.300 --> 15:38.494
WILL:
Oh, come on.

15:38.530 --> 15:40.669
Why not blame the victim for
having pain in the first place?

15:40.700 --> 15:43.066
Yes, but is it true?

15:43.110 --> 15:44.429
The device malfunctioned,
the pain returned.

15:44.470 --> 15:46.233
Only then did Maggie
take the painkillers.

15:46.270 --> 15:47.532
Celeste reverses it
so she can make it

15:47.580 --> 15:49.207
seem like the painkillers
caused the problem.

15:51.350 --> 15:54.319
IfI can get her up to
eight million, will you say yes?

15:54.350 --> 15:55.419
Is she offering
eight million?

15:55.450 --> 15:56.712
Will you accept it?

15:56.750 --> 16:00.356
If you're asking for our
bottom line, then no.

16:00.390 --> 16:02.255
We can't give you
our bottom line

16:02.290 --> 16:05.179
or they'll use it
against us.

16:05.230 --> 16:06.288
(phone chimes)
Where's Kalinda?

16:06.330 --> 16:08.321
I thought she was looking
into their bottom line.

16:08.360 --> 16:10.169
I'll call.
Where are you going?

16:10.200 --> 16:12.418
To meet a reporter.

16:12.470 --> 16:14.461
REPORTER:
Tonight, school officials
are reassuring parents

16:14.500 --> 16:17.333
that all cheese has been removed

16:17.370 --> 16:19.338
from the school lunch menu
for the time being.

16:19.370 --> 16:22.533
It's not yet clear whether
cheese at neighboring schools

16:22.580 --> 16:25.208
and stores in the area
may also be tainted.

16:25.250 --> 16:26.740
Grace!

16:26.780 --> 16:28.645
Stop eating the pizza!

16:28.680 --> 16:30.045
Really?

16:30.090 --> 16:31.409
You were the bad one?

16:31.450 --> 16:34.385
Well, yeah, I was.

16:34.420 --> 16:36.513
Don't I seem like
I was the bad one?

16:36.560 --> 16:38.027
So, in what way bad?

16:38.060 --> 16:40.722
Mm, no, you don't
want to hear this.

16:40.760 --> 16:42.751
No, I do want
to hear this.

16:45.770 --> 16:47.397
Ecstasy.

16:47.440 --> 16:51.399
Driving my car into a lake,
stealing stuff, juvie.

16:51.440 --> 16:52.600
And Mom?

16:52.640 --> 16:55.234
She was perfect.

16:55.280 --> 16:58.147
Homework done, room clean,
never did drugs.

16:58.180 --> 16:59.169
Never did anything.

16:59.210 --> 17:02.043
She's still like that.

17:04.090 --> 17:05.489
She was a good sister.

17:05.520 --> 17:06.589
Always covering for me.

17:06.620 --> 17:08.212
You guys have a good mom.

17:08.260 --> 17:11.184
(hip-hop music playing loudly
in distance)

17:11.230 --> 17:13.653
Grace's tutor.

17:13.700 --> 17:14.792
* Let me take a shot

17:14.830 --> 17:17.196
* I'm 'a sit down, get a drink,
let you work it out *

17:17.230 --> 17:19.460
* Step back, Akinyele,
"Put It in Your Mouth" *

17:19.500 --> 17:21.229
* Have a cocktail, never fail,
turn your body out *

17:21.270 --> 17:22.737
JENNIFER:
The stuff on the staircase!

17:22.770 --> 17:24.135
GRACE (laughs):
Yeah!

17:24.170 --> 17:26.229
Hello!

17:26.270 --> 17:27.737
Hello. Can we turn it down?

17:27.780 --> 17:29.338
(lowers volume)
Sorry.

17:29.380 --> 17:31.507
We're almost done.

17:31.550 --> 17:34.246
So you're the, uh, the tutor?

17:34.280 --> 17:35.372
Uh-huh.

17:35.420 --> 17:36.614
What subject?

17:36.650 --> 17:38.242
Uh, physics.

17:38.290 --> 17:40.383
And just science.

17:40.420 --> 17:42.251
Really?

17:42.290 --> 17:43.757
Where do you go to school?

17:43.790 --> 17:46.122
Uh, U of C.

17:46.160 --> 17:47.752
And, um...

17:47.800 --> 17:49.290
* You deserve every single
dollar *

17:49.330 --> 17:50.399
* And your assets make me
want to... *

17:50.430 --> 17:51.499
What's this?

17:51.530 --> 17:52.758
GRACE:
We're making a video.

17:52.800 --> 17:54.199
We're done with all my homework.

17:54.240 --> 17:55.639
Uh-huh. Got it.

17:55.670 --> 17:57.206
Understood.

17:57.240 --> 17:58.264
(whispers):
Oh, my God.

17:58.310 --> 18:01.279
* Trip down, turn around,
show me what it is *

18:01.310 --> 18:03.346
* Trip down, turn
around, show me what it is *

18:03.380 --> 18:05.439
* Show me what it is,
show me what it is... *

18:05.480 --> 18:08.244
Pretty...

18:08.280 --> 18:09.679
provocative stuff.

18:09.720 --> 18:12.518
(snickers)

18:12.550 --> 18:13.710
It's just street dancing.

18:13.760 --> 18:16.217
Yeah, just freestyle.

18:17.390 --> 18:19.381
(music continues faintly
in distance)

18:22.300 --> 18:24.291
Dad slept with
somebody else.

18:28.300 --> 18:30.530
Dad. He slept with someone
other than the hooker.

18:30.570 --> 18:32.367
He...

18:34.380 --> 18:35.335
How do we know?

18:35.380 --> 18:37.644
He told me.

18:37.680 --> 18:39.307
That's why Mom kicked him out.

18:39.350 --> 18:41.318
You didn't know that?

18:43.320 --> 18:44.844
I didn't know that.

18:50.660 --> 18:52.355
KALINDA: _
What are they saying?

18:52.390 --> 18:54.199
MAN:
They think it was
an improper cleaning

18:54.230 --> 18:55.754
of the culture vats
in Line Six.

18:55.800 --> 18:58.291
You sound like
you don't agree.

18:58.330 --> 19:00.366
Well, I clean Line Six
with peroxyacetic acid

19:00.400 --> 19:02.561
and quaternary ammonium
after every culture.

19:02.600 --> 19:04.431
They're not gonna find
listeria there.

19:04.470 --> 19:06.301
_Where else could
listeria come from?

19:06.340 --> 19:10.606
We keep these units accurate
to one degree either way.

19:10.650 --> 19:13.369
I don't think it was
a refrigeration problem.

19:13.420 --> 19:14.478
So what do you think?

19:14.520 --> 19:18.286
I think it used to be
an easy job to find the source.

19:18.320 --> 19:19.685
Now you got
some of these cheeses--

19:19.720 --> 19:21.608
they're a blend of
three or four lines

19:21.660 --> 19:22.786
from three or four companies.

19:22.820 --> 19:25.823
So all I can say is
goodluck.

19:25.860 --> 19:27.225
Damn. Are you sure?

19:27.260 --> 19:28.750
KALINDA:
Uh, Eli, you know

19:28.800 --> 19:30.461
this is a good thing, right?

19:30.500 --> 19:31.922
It looks like your client isn't
responsible for the listeria.

19:31.970 --> 19:34.461
Kalinda, this is not the law.

19:34.500 --> 19:36.468
I'm not looking for innocence,
I'm looking for certainty.

19:36.500 --> 19:38.832
The whole point is to bury
this story with an apology,

19:38.870 --> 19:40.303
then move on.

19:40.340 --> 19:42.399
So you want our guy
to be guilty?

19:42.440 --> 19:44.476
No, I want it to be over.

19:44.510 --> 19:46.478
I don't want to train
another CEO

19:46.510 --> 19:48.512
from some other company tomorrow
to take the blame.

19:48.550 --> 19:49.869
DIANE:
He can't say this.

19:49.920 --> 19:51.342
He has to say it.

19:51.390 --> 19:53.278
No, he can say, "I
offer my deepest,

19:53.320 --> 19:54.514
sincerest sympathies
to the families."

19:54.560 --> 19:56.312
And, "I'm doing everything I can

19:56.360 --> 19:58.487
to trace the source
of our missteps."
No.

19:58.530 --> 19:59.349
"The source of
the outbreak."

19:59.390 --> 20:01.358
Really? Really, Diane?

20:01.400 --> 20:02.697
He can't say anything that
sounds like an admission...

20:02.730 --> 20:03.662
Really?

20:03.700 --> 20:05.361
I am doing everything I can

20:05.400 --> 20:07.391
to trace the source
of the outbreak.

20:07.440 --> 20:09.897
Heather Farms is committed
to finding the root of this...

20:09.940 --> 20:11.669
So why should I hold your story?

20:11.710 --> 20:13.871
WILL:
Well, the
Scotch for one.

20:13.910 --> 20:15.434
And because it's not true.

20:15.480 --> 20:17.505
It's not true that Dr. Farland's
being investigated?

20:17.550 --> 20:18.448
No, it's not true

20:18.480 --> 20:20.573
the investigation
is going Farland's way.

20:20.620 --> 20:22.372
And you know this how?

20:22.420 --> 20:24.615
I know this because I can see
who has an agenda.

20:24.650 --> 20:26.515
In this case, the defense.
MAN:
Heads up.

20:26.550 --> 20:27.949
Why should I care?

20:27.990 --> 20:29.480
Because I can
make you care.

20:29.520 --> 20:31.954
Okay.

20:31.990 --> 20:34.424
I'll give you complete
back channel on the case.

20:34.460 --> 20:35.552
(chuckles)

20:35.600 --> 20:38.569
Uh, as pulse-racing
as that is,

20:38.600 --> 20:40.591
get me back channel on this.

20:40.640 --> 20:41.664
Your computer?

20:41.700 --> 20:43.361
Mm, no, the cheese thing.

20:43.410 --> 20:45.264
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

20:45.310 --> 20:46.436
The listeria outbreak.

20:46.470 --> 20:49.337
All the sick kids,
some were hospitalized...

20:49.380 --> 20:51.371
Eli Gold is
part of your firm, right?

20:54.780 --> 20:57.340
I'll delay my story,
you get me

20:57.390 --> 20:59.381
the back channel ticktock
on the crisis managing.

20:59.420 --> 21:00.956
I'll have to talk to Eli.

21:00.990 --> 21:05.552
Well, then it wouldn't be
a back channel, would it?

21:05.590 --> 21:07.421
Get me something
behind the scenes.

21:07.460 --> 21:10.793
Let me see what I can do.

21:12.470 --> 21:14.665
it's not the FDA investigation
that's concluding.

21:14.700 --> 21:15.894
What do you mean?

21:15.940 --> 21:17.305
The call I got

21:17.340 --> 21:18.659
was about the State's Attorney.

21:18.710 --> 21:19.859
Turns out,

21:19.910 --> 21:23.038
they decided not to bring fraud
charges against Dr. Farland.

21:31.690 --> 21:33.009
Hello.

21:33.050 --> 21:34.415
May I help you?

21:34.460 --> 21:35.449
You may.

21:35.490 --> 21:38.459
I need information
about a fraud investigation.

21:44.970 --> 21:46.528
Are you sure?
Am I sure I have

21:46.570 --> 21:48.595
nothing to offer you about our
fraud investigation? I am.

21:48.640 --> 21:50.403
We just need to
know if this leak

21:50.440 --> 21:52.533
to Gretchen Battista was
faked, Cary, that's all.

21:52.570 --> 21:55.004
And if it was, then we need
to get her to hold her story.

21:55.040 --> 21:57.372
I understand.

21:57.410 --> 21:58.672
I still have nothing.

22:00.980 --> 22:02.948
How have you been?

22:02.980 --> 22:05.778
Oh, come on.

22:05.820 --> 22:08.618
Kalinda, you can fake somebody
else, but you can't fake me.

22:08.660 --> 22:10.525
What am I faking?

22:10.560 --> 22:11.652
Interest,

22:11.690 --> 22:13.999
concern,
friendship.

22:14.030 --> 22:15.497
And what if I'm not?

22:15.530 --> 22:17.623
Then let's be friends.

22:17.670 --> 22:18.728
(sighs)

22:18.770 --> 22:19.964
But I still don't have
anything for you

22:20.000 --> 22:21.092
about this fraud
investigation.

22:21.140 --> 22:22.596
Check with Matan;
it's his case.

22:22.640 --> 22:23.732
Hmm, he's no use.

22:23.770 --> 22:24.998
Because he doesn't want
to sleep With you?

22:26.540 --> 22:28.531
But you do?

22:29.580 --> 22:31.571
I'm merely making
an observation.

22:31.610 --> 22:33.475
And what observation
might that be?

22:33.520 --> 22:34.976
You tend to _use
people's feelings

22:35.020 --> 22:37.011
to further_
your investigations.

22:40.760 --> 22:42.751
You think that's
what I did with you?

22:43.790 --> 22:46.623
I think I have
to get back to work.

22:46.660 --> 22:49.549
Cary, whatever I felt,
I didn't invent.

22:49.600 --> 22:50.919
That's great
to know, Kalinda.

22:50.970 --> 22:53.689
Now I have to get back to work
and I think you do, too.

22:55.970 --> 22:57.961
Yeah.

23:00.710 --> 23:02.837
NEWSCASTER:
The CEO questioned the need

23:02.880 --> 23:04.848
to recall all cheese products,
suggesting

23:04.880 --> 23:06.871
that the listeria victims
themselves

23:06.910 --> 23:09.014
could have been responsible
for the sickness.

23:09.050 --> 23:10.813
I don't know that much
about it at this point,

23:10.850 --> 23:13.683
but I-I would love to know
what else those kids were eating

23:13.720 --> 23:15.119
because I don't think
it's just the cheese.

23:15.160 --> 23:16.286
Excuse me.

23:16.320 --> 23:18.083
Look, I think it's a little
premature at this point...

23:18.130 --> 23:20.189
What the hell?

23:20.230 --> 23:21.527
What the hell?!

23:21.560 --> 23:23.562
What did you say?

23:23.600 --> 23:25.522
What did you say?

23:25.570 --> 23:26.662
What are you
talking about?

23:26.700 --> 23:27.792
I-I said exactly
what you told me...

23:27.840 --> 23:30.161
"I don't know enough, but
what else did these kids eat"?

23:30.200 --> 23:32.430
You know what you do
when you don't know enough?

23:32.470 --> 23:33.630
You shut
the hell up.

23:33.680 --> 23:34.772
I didn't say that.

23:34.810 --> 23:36.038
With a garbage bag
in your hand?

